text: I dont know, i was hoping you would help me outline the skills I need

Joking, curious about how the world would function if we have no traditions holding us back

What about your life are you pondering?? I suppose I want to learn about how to build a successful business, and I'm also interested in figuring out how the world works ... politics / war / travel ... so I try to get more clued up on it every day and that's what helped me come up with my business idea and start my own business

I can list the skills that I used the most in engineering and then maybe next to it you rate yourself out of 10 how you think you score in them ... then I can help you build the ones that you are lacking

Engineering skills I used VERY REGULARLY:
>*1) Problem solving:* Always trying to break down complex problems into small manageable parts to try to come up with a solution


>*2) Communication:* I can't emphasize this one enough. Being able to communicate clearly, CONCISELY (i.e. not sending long-ass emails to my team, but concise summaries for people to understand where they stand and bullet pointed next steps required. Also having to communicate complex things in plain English to non-technical people is very important


>*3) Teamwork:* Always working in teams across different functions to complete projects. Have to be sociable in order to get the most / best out of people and keep them motivated.


>*4) Organisation:* Having to be a good project manager to keep the projects on track and the team enthusiastic and driving towards deadlines


>*5) Technical knowledge:* Of course needing to grasp difficult technical concepts (may be mathematical or otherwise) and willingness to continuously learn from mistakes
